revision.text:
==Latin==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|la|sanguen}}

===Etymology===
Originally ''sanguīs'', from older {{term|sanguen|lang=la}}, from {{term/t|la|*san-}} (compare {{term|sanies|saniēs|lang=la}} ‘[[ichor]]; ulcer’), from {{etyl|ine-pro|la}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*h₁sh₂-én-}}, oblique stem of {{term/t|ine-pro|*h₁ésh₂r̥||blood}}; cf. Old Latin {{term|assyr|lang=la}}, {{term|aser|lang=la}}, Hittite {{term|𒌍𒄩𒅈|lang=hit|tr=ešḫar}}, Sanskrit {{term|असृज्|tr=ásṛk|lang=sa}}, Ancient Greek {{term|ἔαρ|lang=grc|tr=ear}}, Old Armenian {{term|արիւն|sc=Armn|tr=ariwn|lang=xcl}}. The original paradigm must have been nominative {{term|assyr|lang=la}}, oblique ''san-'', which then split into doublets. The element -''guen'' is probably from {{term|unguen|lang=la}}, {{term|inguen|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Classical}} {{IPA|/ˈsaŋ.ɡwis/|lang=la}}
